The paper discusses the design and planning strategies for a long-term user commitment and how to evaluate results for cultural mobile applications, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of textual, visual, and audio means to convey cultural heritage, which could fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the production and distribution of a mobile app, which could fall under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Cybernetics (cs.CY).
